trans-unit.source: Principal Component Analysis
trans-unit.target: Principal Component Analysis

trans-unit.source: Computes a set of features with reduced dimensionality for more efficient learning
trans-unit.target: Computes a set of features with reduced dimensionality for more efficient learning

trans-unit.source: Module Overview
trans-unit.target: Module Overview

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Principal Component Analysis</ui> module to analyze your data and create a reduced feature set that captures all the information contained in the larger dataset.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Principal Component Analysis</ui> module to analyze your data and create a reduced feature set that captures all the information contained in the larger dataset.

trans-unit.source: The module also creates a transformation that you can apply to new data, to achieve a similar reduction in dimensionality and compression of features, without requiring additional training.
trans-unit.target: The module also creates a transformation that you can apply to new data, to achieve a similar reduction in dimensionality and compression of features, without requiring additional training.

trans-unit.source: Understanding Principal Component Analysis
trans-unit.target: Understanding Principal Component Analysis

trans-unit.source: Principal Component Analysis is based on the fact that many types of vector-space data are compressible, and that compression can be most efficiently achieved by sampling.
trans-unit.target: Principal Component Analysis is based on the fact that many types of vector-space data are compressible, and that compression can be most efficiently achieved by sampling.

trans-unit.source: As such, Principal Component Analysis (PCA) is a popular technique in machine learning for dimensionality reduction.
trans-unit.target: As such, Principal Component Analysis (PCA) is a popular technique in machine learning for dimensionality reduction.

trans-unit.source: Added benefits are that PCA can improve data visualization and optimize resource utilization by the learning algorithm.
trans-unit.target: Added benefits are that PCA can improve data visualization and optimize resource utilization by the learning algorithm.

trans-unit.source: The <ui>Principal Component Analysis</ui> module transforms a set of feature columns in the provided dataset into a projection of the feature space that has lower dimensionality.
trans-unit.target: The <ui>Principal Component Analysis</ui> module transforms a set of feature columns in the provided dataset into a projection of the feature space that has lower dimensionality.

trans-unit.source: By definition, the transformed data matrices capture the variance in the original data while reducing the effect of noise and minimizing the risk of overfitting.
trans-unit.target: By definition, the transformed data matrices capture the variance in the original data while reducing the effect of noise and minimizing the risk of overfitting.

trans-unit.source: The algorithm uses randomization techniques to identify a feature subspace that captures most of the information in the complete feature matrix.
trans-unit.target: The algorithm uses randomization techniques to identify a feature subspace that captures most of the information in the complete feature matrix.

trans-unit.source: How to Configure Principal Component Analysis
trans-unit.target: How to Configure Principal Component Analysis

trans-unit.source: Add the dataset you want to analyze, and connect it to the input of the module.
trans-unit.target: Add the dataset you want to analyze, and connect it to the input of the module.

trans-unit.source: If it is not already clear which columns are features and which are labels, we recommend that you use the <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link> module to mark the columns in advance.
trans-unit.target: If it is not already clear which columns are features and which are labels, we recommend that you use the <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link> module to mark the columns in advance.

trans-unit.source: Choose the columns to analyze.
trans-unit.target: Choose the columns to analyze.

trans-unit.source: Specify how many dimensions to include in the output dataset.
trans-unit.target: Specify how many dimensions to include in the output dataset.

trans-unit.source: The algorithm used for this module is optimized when the number of reduced dimensions is much smaller than the original dimensions.
trans-unit.target: The algorithm used for this module is optimized when the number of reduced dimensions is much smaller than the original dimensions.

trans-unit.source: Run the experiment.
trans-unit.target: Run the experiment.

trans-unit.source: The module outputs a reduced set of columns that you can use in creating a model.
trans-unit.target: The module outputs a reduced set of columns that you can use in creating a model.

trans-unit.source: You can save the output as a new dataset or use it in your experiment.
trans-unit.target: You can save the output as a new dataset or use it in your experiment.

trans-unit.source: For example, if the source dataset has eight columns and you type <userInput>3</userInput>, three new columns will be returned that capture the information of the eight selected columns.
trans-unit.target: For example, if the source dataset has eight columns and you type <userInput>3</userInput>, three new columns will be returned that capture the information of the eight selected columns.

trans-unit.source: In that case, the columns would be named Col1, Col2, and Col3, and should be considered an approximation of the contents of columns 1-8, rather than being directly derived from particular source columns.
trans-unit.target: In that case, the columns would be named Col1, Col2, and Col3, and should be considered an approximation of the contents of columns 1-8, rather than being directly derived from particular source columns.

trans-unit.source: In other words, columns the contents of the original selected columns are compressed into a new set of columns.
trans-unit.target: In other words, columns the contents of the original selected columns are compressed into a new set of columns.

trans-unit.source: Optionally, you can save the analysis process as a saved transform, to apply to another dataset using <link xlink:href="805e592d-0f1f-48eb-97c9-688ed0c1dc70" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Apply Transformation</link>.
trans-unit.target: Optionally, you can save the analysis process as a saved transform, to apply to another dataset using <link xlink:href="805e592d-0f1f-48eb-97c9-688ed0c1dc70" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Apply Transformation</link>.

trans-unit.source: Note that the dataset you apply the transformation to must have the same schema as the original dataset.
trans-unit.target: Note that the dataset you apply the transformation to must have the same schema as the original dataset.
